Upon that worthily admired patriot, and honour of his country the Observator
4 p.
Printed for A. Harris, London : 1684.
Caption title. Imprint from colophon. A light poem in praise of Roger L'Estrange. At head of title: [Line of Greek] In English, To undo a city is an easie matter even for the wicked; but to set it right again is difficult. Item at reel 584:5 identified as Wing U106A (number cancelled). Reproductions of original in Henry E. Huntington Library and Art Gallery. Includes bibliographical references.
